::Prowl::

Prowl nodded and looked at Cliffjumper. "Lets go do that. Get as many
as you can, but first go heal your self."

He points to the Element. "That's the ship. The shields should let you
pass. If not, ask them to let you in over comm."

(I have no idea if the shields will let Cliffjumper or anyone pass, so
you should ask anyways.)

He flies off toward the Groove, landing near the bot and picking him
up and then flying toward Streetwise to get that bot too.



--- In nbwrpg@y..., "Megan Solmonson" <tmrattrap@h...> wrote:

> * Iron sighed, shaking her head and finally FINALLY clearing it.
> So instead of anger, sadness, she discovered that she was fine.
> < Mood swing.>
> Well, come to think of it she had had some pains in her stomach a
night or 
> two ago but she also hadn't eaten anything in the longest of time.
> But she had been mean and she looked over her shoulder at Prowl with
a sorry 
> look on her face.
> < I'm sorry, things are just getting to me.>
> But then she turned her eyes back towards the field, the evening
closing in 
> and orange light spilling onto the , black siluets fighting.
> Even though she had began to hate battle, the sight was rather 
> beautiful...if you forgot the sounds of gunshots and battle cries.
> She almost seemed lost in the sight for a few moments, arm hanging
limp at 
> her side, her eye looking dark and far away.
> But she answered Prowl, none the less.*
> 
> " Yes, take them all in and make sure they're regenerated."
